						<summary>

						<p>On a stone built into the outer entrance of the Mahishāsuramardini temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 172[6], Krōdhana, Māgha, śu. 5, Friday.</p>						

						<p>States that the foundation was laid on the above date for the <hi rend="italic">navadvāra-gōpura</hi> in the temple of the goddess, which was consecrated by Rāja Yērlagaḍḍa Aṅkinēḍu, in Śaka 1721, Raudri, Chaitra, śu. 5, Sunday.</p>						

						</summary>
